%N A084678 a(n) = b(n,n) with b(n,1) = n and b(n,k) = binomial(b(n,k-1),d(n,n-k+1)) for 1<k<=n, where d(n,i) are the divisors of n, d(i)<d(j), 1<=i<j<=A000005(n).
%H A084678 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A084678/b084678.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..23</a>
%F A084678 a(p) = p, p prime.
%e A084678 Set of divisors of n=10: {1,2,5,10}, binomial(10,5)=252 -> binomial(252,2)=31626 -> binomial(31626,1)=31626=a(10).
